      "span_text": "The phycobilisome is an adaptive structure which can alter the light harvesting capabilities of the cell depending upon the by light intensity, quality, and nutrient However, currently white LEDs, which are produced using blue LEDs with phosphor coatings, are less efficient than the single-wave-peak LEDs  , therefore an economic assessment must be considered for the viable production of marketable products."
